headline: Future-ready power companies are seizing the advantages of a soft market, according to the Willis Power Market Review
summary: LONDON, Sept. 11, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- After years of navigating tough market conditions, power companies are beginning to see relief. Capacity is returning, competition among insurers is intensifying and pricing is easing, shifting the balance decisively in favour of buyers, according to the Power Market Review published today by Willis, a WTW business (NASDAQ: WTW).
